user_question: How do I grow a Venus flytrap indoors and generate an image of a Venus flytrap catching an insect?
final_answer: To grow a Venus flytrap indoors: 1) Use a pot with drainage holes. 2) Use a soil mix of sphagnum moss and sand. 3) Provide bright, indirect sunlight. 4) Water with distilled water. 5) Maintain high humidity. Image of a Venus flytrap catching an insect generated. You can feed it small live insects such as flies, spiders, crickets, and beetles.
